7. PROGRAM FOR EXCEPTION HANDLING FOR ZERO DIVISION
package shape;
import java.util.Scanner;

public class DivisionByZeroHandling {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        try {
            // Take two integers as input
            System.out.print("Enter numerator: ");
            int num1 = sc.nextInt();

            System.out.print("Enter denominator: ");
            int num2 = sc.nextInt();

            // Try dividing inside try block
            int result = num1 / num2;

            // Print result if division is valid
            System.out.println("Result: " + result);
        } 
        catch (ArithmeticException e) {
            // Handle division by zero
            System.out.println("Exception handled: Division by zero is not allowed.");
        }

        sc.close();
        }}
OUTPUT:
TEST CASE 1:
Enter numerator: 10
Enter denominator: 2
Result: 5
TEST CASE 2:
Enter numerator: 20
Enter denominator: 0
Result: Exception handled
TEST CASE 3:
Enter numerator: -5
Enter denominator: 5
Result: -1
TEST CASE 4:
Enter numerator: 0
Enter denominator: 3
Result: 0
TEST CASE 5:
Enter numerator: 100
Enter denominator: -10
Result: -10
RESULT:
Program gracefully handles division by zero and displays a custom message.
